---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Writing | Motunrayo Koyejo" 
  currentPage="writing"
>
  <header style="padding: 80px 0 20px;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="eyebrow">Writing</div>
      <h1>Thinking out loud about <em>African fintech</em>.</h1>
      <p class="lede">Most of what I write comes back to the same thing: the unglamorous infrastructure we still need to build before African fintech lives up to its promise. I don't write often. I write when something's been nagging at me long enough that I have to put it down somewhere.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Published <em>articles</em></h2>

      <a class="article" href="https://techeconomy.ng/until-we-fix-cross-border-payments-africas-trade-dream-is-a-mirage/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <div class="article-meta">Tech Economy · 2025</div>
        <div class="article-title">Until we fix cross-border payments, Africa's trade dream is a mirage</div>
        <div class="article-excerpt">We've been talking about a single trading bloc across this continent for years. But every time a Lagos merchant tries to pay a supplier in Nairobi, the payment rails quietly remind us we aren't there yet. A piece on the bottleneck everyone talks around, and what it would actually take to fix.</div>
      </a>

      <a class="article" href="https://techeconomy.ng/how-open-banking-apis-can-revolutionize-fintech-in-africa/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <div class="article-meta">Tech Economy · 2025</div>
        <div class="article-title">How open banking APIs can revolutionise fintech in Africa</div>
        <div class="article-excerpt">What if you could actually see all your money across all your banks and apps in one place, and give apps permission to work with it? It sounds simple. The engineering and regulatory work to make it real is anything but.</div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="cta-band">
        <h3>More on the way.</h3>
        <p>I'm slowly building a more regular writing habit: shorter pieces on backend engineering, fintech, and the things I'm currently learning. Check back now and then, or follow along on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/motunrayokoyejo/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color: var(--accent);">LinkedIn</a> where I tend to think out loud first.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>